dc_description_s: Ayres Associates provided the North Central Wisconsin Regional Planning Commission (NCWRPC) with digital orthoimagery services in 2014 and 2015 as part of the Wisconsin Regional Orthophotography Consortium (WROC). The coverage area included 41 counties in Wisconsin and was flown in spring 2014 and spring 2015 under leaf-off conditions. Resultant orthoimagery was rectified to new DEMs created from the acquired imagery and existing LiDAR where available. 18-inch pixel resolution orthoimagery was delivered in county mosaics (MrSID) and DOQQs (GeoTIFF) by county.

uw_supplemental_s: Imagery from WROC was acquired across two years. Counties flown in 2014: Buffalo, Chippewa, Kewaunee, Trempealeau.  The remainder were flown in 2015.
